  "suggestion": "[neuroscience+Bayesian-inference+information-theory+Karl-Friston] REFINEMENT — Free Energy Minimization, made implementable: represent each person as a generative model with three components: (1) priors = weighted beliefs about world-states {safety, status, meaning, bodily-state}, (2) likelihood = how strongly the situation updates each prior, (3) behavior = the action that minimizes expected surprise across all priors simultaneously. Emotion = signed prediction-error per prior (positive = relief/joy, negative = threat/grief). Cognition = the precision-weighting that determines which prior dominates. This collapses Active Inference into a single `predict` call: score each prior's violation, weight by precision, output dominant emotion + the behavior that would restore equilibrium. — Math: F = E_q[log q(s) - log p(s,o)] — minimize variational free energy; behavior selects action a* = argmin_a F(a); [dynamical-systems+topology+catastrophe-theory+René-Thom] Catastrophe Surface Model — map all human behavioral/emotional transitions onto René Thom's cusp catastrophe surface. Two control parameters: arousal (physiological activation) and conflict (goal interference). One state variable: behavioral mode (approach vs. avoidance). The cusp geometry explains sudden qualitative shifts that linear models cannot: panic attacks, falling in love, polarization, insight moments, addiction relapse. Implementation: given a situation, compute (arousal, conflict) coordinates, look up position on cusp surface, return current behavioral mode and whether the system is near a fold (transition risk). The entire model is one polynomial: V = x^4 + ax^2 + bx. — Math: Cusp potential V(x; a,b) = x^4/4 + ax^2/2 + bx; equilibria where dV/dx = 0; fold catastrophe where d²V/dx² = 0; [control-theory+physiology+allostasis+dynamical-systems] Homeostatic Stack — human psychology as a hierarchy of regulated variables with setpoints, borrowed from control theory and physiology. Seven stacked regulators: {body-state, safety, attachment, status, agency, coherence, meaning}. Each has a setpoint and current reading. Behavior is always the single action that reduces the largest weighted deficit. Emotion is the error signal for each layer (fear=safety-deficit, shame=status-deficit, anxiety=coherence-deficit, depression=multi-layer chronic deficit). Cognition is the model the system uses to predict which actions will restore setpoints. This is compact (7 numbers + weights), unified (one mechanism explains all motivation), and maps directly to Maslow, Panksepp's SEEKING system, and Terror Management Theory — but as a control system, not a list. — Math: deficit_i = |setpoint_i - current_i| × weight_i; action* = argmax_a Σ_i reduction_i(a); emotion_i = f(deficit_i, Δdeficit_i)",
